; Version identifiers
; The specification for HAL devices says:
;   "[The version] consists of a major version number (bits 31-16) and a minor
;   version number (bits 15-0). A change in major version number indicates an
;   incompatible change of API. An increase in the minor version number
;   indicates backwards-compatible extensions to the API (eg extra functions)."
; The implication is that any given generation of a device driver must not
; attempt to drive a device of any /major/ version it does not recognise, but
; subject thereto, if it knows how to drive a /minor/ version x, and the device
; reports minor version y where y >= x, then they should work together
; correctly, if perhaps not optimally. Another way of putting this is that
; a new minor version is appropriate if the device offers additional
; /capabilities/ to the device driver, but not if it places additional
; /requirements/ on it: thus the "eg extra functions" clause is not a
; sufficient criterion in itself. In light of this, the "HasTrigger"
; extension should in retrospect have been assigned a new major version
; instead, but we are now stuck with this anomaly.
                                        ^       0
HALDeviceSDHCI_MajorVersion_Original    #       &10000  ; 0
HALDeviceSDHCI_MajorVersion_Soft        #       &10000  ; 1
HALDeviceSDHCI_MajorVersion_Soft2       #       &10000  ; 2
; Minor versions for MajorVersion_Original
                                                ^       0
HALDeviceSDHCI_MinorVersion_Original            #       1       ; 0
HALDeviceSDHCI_MinorVersion_OriginalHasTrigger  #       1       ; 1
HALDeviceSDHCI_MinorVersion_OriginalValidDevNo  #       1       ; 2
HALDeviceSDHCI_MinorVersion_HasTrigger          *       HALDeviceSDHCI_MinorVersion_OriginalHasTrigger ; backward-compatible name
; Minor versions for MajorVersion_Soft
                                                ^       0
HALDeviceSDHCI_MinorVersion_Soft                #       1       ; 0
HALDeviceSDHCI_MinorVersion_SoftValidDevNo      #       1       ; 1
; Minor versions for MajorVersion_Soft2
                                                ^       0
HALDeviceSDHCI_MinorVersion_Soft2               #       1       ; 0

